{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-20355/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-20355"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["2:03:55"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["two shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["The title \"Phantom Thread\" appears over a shot of a man tailoring a woman's dress."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-20355","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-20355"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1/97be8563-12fc-4f64-ad0d-8e64cd2bec4f","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:02:26.396Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The typeface used here is one designed by Reynolds Stone, a famous British engraver and typographer. Daniel Day-Lewis's family was close to Stone and Day-Lewis named Reynolds after him. Day-Lewis speaks about Stone (and meets his granddaughter) in an interview available <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW145689552 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ro9bS5A-8j8\"><u>here</u></a>.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:172.9373504784689,270.2825956937799,1608.3126495215308,521.2881279904304"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1/e350e380-0de6-4c03-94cd-025e0b0e3527","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:03:25.436Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In one of the snippets of Alma’s conversation with Dr. Hardy, she tells her interlocutor that she can stand longer than anyone else; in other words, that she can both be Reynolds’s muse better than any other woman and that she can resist his demanding nature. Accordingly, the film ends with a brief <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW63905618 BCX4\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-03435.html\"><u>callback</u></a> to that moment in her conversation with Dr. Hardy. As the film transitions to the end credits with this shot, Alma remains standing forever in an affirmation of her confident words and her devotion to Reynolds and his art.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20355/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:697.4955143540667,106.13486842105266,514.4452751196173,926.1064593301434"}}}]}]}]}